    "LLMs exhibit label bias even on tasks with semantically equivalent labels, such as multi-choice question answering.",
    "notable gains in bias, unless the imbalance is very extreme-specifically, when the demonstrations include only a single or no demonstrations for one of the labels (p Ò ą 0.75).",
    "Interestingly, model performance follows the same trends (Fig. 5c).",
    "Overall, our results indicate that for most tasks, the impact of label imbalance in the demonstrations set is minimal, except for cases of severe imbalance.",
